AN elderly couple was found dead in their small house after they were last seen alive shopping a week before Christmas 2020. Madala Nicholas and gogo Hilary Smith were found dead in their home in Clonee near Fethard in Ireland after neighbours grew concerned that their car had not been moved for some time. Cops have been studying a large amounts of documents that were found in the couple’s home. According to the Mirror, technical examinations of a cellphone and a laptop found in the house have so far not revealed any call, SMS or email activity that would suggest that either of the couple were alive later than December, 17 2020. READ: GOGO AND MKHULU CELEBRATE 100TH BIRTHDAY! Madala Nicholas, who was a retired sea captain who worked on cruise ships in Australia, would have been 81 at that stage, while gogo Hilary, who also worked on cruise ships, would have been 78. Cops were alerted to the home after a neighbour, who thought the couple had sold the house and moved, noticed their car parked around the back. When cops went to the house to carry out a welfare check, they discovered madala Nicholas’ body in a bedroom and gogo Hilary’s in the sitting room. It was clear that both had been dead for several months. Erin Research founder, Padraic Grennan, confirmed on Monday, 11 July that his investigators had found that Madala Nicholas had a 61-year-old son from a previous relationship and that he had a brother living in London. Madala Nicholas’ brother told his team that he had not been in contact with his brother for more than 25 years, as he had been working at sea.